      • ModuleElement

        public ModuleElement(String name,
                     String comment,
                     URI location,
                     Collection<? extends ConstantAliasProxy> constantAliasList,
                     Collection<? extends EventDeclProxy> eventDeclList,
                     Collection<? extends Proxy> eventAliasList,
                     Collection<? extends Proxy> componentList)
        Creates a new module.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the new module.
        comment - The comment of the new module, or null.
        location - The location of the new module.
        constantAliasList - The constant definition list of the new module, or null if empty.
        eventDeclList - The event declaration list of the new module, or null if empty.
        eventAliasList - The event alias list of the new module, or null if empty. Each element is of type AliasProxy or ForeachProxy.
        componentList - The component list of the new module, or null if empty. Each element is of type ComponentProxy or ForeachProxy.

      • ModuleElement

        public ModuleElement(String name,
                     URI location)
        Creates a new module using default values. This constructor creates a module with the comment set to null, an empty constant definition list, an empty event declaration list, an empty event alias list, and an empty component list.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the new module.
        location - The location of the new module.

      • getProxyInterface

        public Class<ModuleProxy> getProxyInterface()
        Description copied from interface: Proxy
        Returns the most specific proxy interface implemented by this object. This method must return one of the leaf interfaces of the proxy hierarchy, e.g. EventProxy, not any specific implementation class. This can be used by equality visitors to ensure that objects from different implementations are considered as equal.
        Specified by:

      • getComponentList

        public List<Proxy> getComponentList()
        Description copied from interface: ModuleProxy
        Gets the component list of this module. This list does not only contain the automata (SimpleComponentProxy) of the module, but also all EFA variables (VariableComponentProxy) and module instances (InstanceProxy). All these items can be nested in foreach blocks (ForeachProxy).
        Specified by:
        getComponentList in interface ModuleProxy
        Returns:
        The component list. Each element is of type ComponentProxy or ForeachProxy.
